<\/a><\/span><\/div>\n<nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 eztoc-toggle-hide-by-default' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/oral-and-maxillofacial-surgeon\/#Definition_Oral_and_Maxillofacial_Surgeon\" title=\"Definition| Oral and Maxillofacial Surgeon\">Definition| Oral and Maxillofacial Surgeon<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/oral-and-maxillofacial-surgeon\/#Common_Surgeries_an_oral_and_maxillofacial_surgeon_carryout\" title=\"Common Surgeries an oral and maxillofacial surgeon carryout\">Common Surgeries an oral and maxillofacial surgeon carryout<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/oral-and-maxillofacial-surgeon\/#Major_areas_of_OMS_practice\" title=\"Major areas of OMS practice\">Major areas of OMS practice<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/oral-and-maxillofacial-surgeon\/#Career_Definition\" title=\"Career Definition\">Career Definition<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/oral-and-maxillofacial-surgeon\/#High_School_subjects_required_Oral_and_Maxillofacial_Surgeon\" title=\"High School subjects required| Oral and Maxillofacial Surgeon\">High School subjects required| Oral and Maxillofacial Surgeon<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/oral-and-maxillofacial-surgeon\/#How_to_become_a_maxillofacial_surgeon\" title=\"How to become a maxillofacial surgeon\">How to become a maxillofacial surgeon<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/oral-and-maxillofacial-surgeon\/#Supportive_electives_to_take_in_high_school_that_arrange_you_for_this_profession\" title=\"Supportive electives to take in high school that arrange you for this profession\">Supportive electives to take in high school that arrange you for this profession<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n\n<p style=\"padding-left: 80px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><strong> Maxillofacial surgeons, sometimes called oral and maxillofacial surgeons, are trained to handle a wide variety of conditions and injuries learn more below.<\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-2283 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/09\/oral-and-maxillofacial-surgery-300x223.jpg\" alt=\"Oral and Maxillofacial Surgeon\" width=\"300\" height=\"223\" title=\"\"><\/p>\n<p><strong>Contents<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #993300;\"><a style=\"color: #993300;\" href=\"#_Toc83042340\">Definition<\/a><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #993300;\"><a style=\"color: #993300;\" href=\"#_Toc83042341\">Common Surgeries an oral and maxillofacial surgeon carryout<\/a><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #993300;\"><a style=\"color: #993300;\" href=\"#_Toc83042342\">Major areas of OMS practice<\/a><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #993300;\"><a style=\"color: #993300;\" href=\"#_Toc83042343\">Career Definition <\/a><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #993300;\"><a style=\"color: #993300;\" href=\"#_Toc83042344\">High School subjects required<\/a><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #993300;\">How to become a maxillofacial surgeon<\/span><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc83042346\"><span style=\"color: #993300;\">Supportive electives to take in high school that arrange you for this profession<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n<h2 id=\"definition-oral-and-maxillofacial-surgeon\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Definition_Oral_and_Maxillofacial_Surgeon\"><\/span><a name=\"_Toc83042340\"><\/a>Definition| Oral and Maxillofacial Surgeon<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Maxillary surgery is a unique specialty that merges medical and dental science.<\/p>\n<h2 id=\"common-surgeries-an-oral-and-maxillofacial-surgeon-carryout\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Common_Surgeries_an_oral_and_maxillofacial_surgeon_carryout\"><\/span><a name=\"_Toc83042341\"><\/a>Common Surgeries an oral and maxillofacial surgeon carryout<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Some of the most common oral and maxillofacial surgeries include the following:<\/li>\n<li data-wp-editing=\"1\">Wisdom teeth management and extraction<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-2282 alignright\" src=\"https:\/\/www.applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/09\/wisdom-tooth-300x172.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"172\" title=\"\"><\/li>\n<li>Facial injury and trauma surgery<\/li>\n<li>Oral, Head, and Neck cancer treatment<\/li>\n<li>Surgery corrections of the jaw<\/li>\n<li>Surgery of the cleft Lip and plastic surgery<\/li>\n<li>TMJ disorders and facial pain treatment.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2 id=\"major-areas-of-oms-practice\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Major_areas_of_OMS_practice\"><\/span><a name=\"_Toc83042342\"><\/a>Major areas of OMS practice<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Anesthesia<\/li>\n<li>Dentoalveolar surgery<\/li>\n<li>Dental implants<\/li>\n<li>Surgical modification of maxillofacial skeletal deformities<\/li>\n<li>Orthognathic Surgery<\/li>\n<li>Cleft and Craniofacial Surgery<\/li>\n<li>Maxillofacial Trauma.<\/li>\n<li>Temporomandibular Joint.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2 id=\"career-definition\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Career_Definition\"><\/span><a name=\"_Toc83042343\"><\/a>Career Definition<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"132\"><strong><em>Education<\/em><\/strong><\/td>\n<td width=\"384\"><strong><em>Doctor of Dental Surgery degree<\/em><\/strong><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"132\">Job Skills<\/td>\n<td width=\"384\">Dexterity, interpersonal communication, leadership, organization<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"132\">Median Salary<\/td>\n<td width=\"384\">$208,000 and above (oral and maxillofacial surgeons)<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"132\">Job Growth<\/td>\n<td width=\"384\">2% (oral and maxillofacial surgeons)<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h2 id=\"high-school-subjects-required-oral-and-maxillofacial-surgeon\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"High_School_subjects_required_Oral_and_Maxillofacial_Surgeon\"><\/span><a name=\"_Toc83042344\"><\/a>High School subjects required| Oral and Maxillofacial Surgeon<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><strong><em>They a subject includes:<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Biology and advanced placement (AP) Biology<\/li>\n<li>Chemistry and AP chemistry<\/li>\n<li>Physics and AP chemistry<\/li>\n<li>Elective such as Genetics, Human Anatomy and Physiology, Biotechnology, Engineering, Bioethics, etc.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-become-a-maxillofacial-surgeon\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"How_to_become_a_maxillofacial_surgeon\"><\/span><a name=\"_Toc83042345\"><\/a>How to become a maxillofacial surgeon<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-2285 alignright\" src=\"https:\/\/www.applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/09\/dental-implantations-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"Oral and Maxillofacial Surgeon\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" title=\"\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Two to four years of undergraduate study (BS, BA, or equivalent degrees)<\/li>\n<li>Four years dental study (DMD, BDent, DDS or BDS).<\/li>\n<li>Four to six years residency training (six years includes two additional years for acquiring a medical degree).<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2 id=\"supportive-electives-to-take-in-high-school-that-arrange-you-for-this-profession\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Supportive_electives_to_take_in_high_school_that_arrange_you_for_this_profession\"><\/span><a name=\"_Toc83042346\"><\/a>Supportive electives to take in high school that arrange you for this profession<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><strong><em>They include:<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Anatomy and physiology<\/li>\n<li>Computer application<\/li>\n<li>Introduction to Health Care<\/li>\n<li>Nursing<\/li>\n<li>Safety and First Aid<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333399;\"><strong>See also&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;<\/strong><\/span><a title=\"Australian Health and Medical Research\" href=\"https:\/\/www.applyjobs.org.ng\/australian-health-and-medical-research\/\" rel=\"bookmark nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: #333399;\"><strong>Australian Health and Medical Research<\/strong><\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"Oral and Maxillofacial Surgeon, Definition Majors areas of OMS practice, career Definition for an oral surgeons, High school&hellip;\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":2284,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[14],"tags":[728],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2281"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=2281"}],"version-history":[{"count":1,"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2281\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":19033,"href"